8‑Week Syllabus at a glance

Week 1

BA Foundations & Stakeholder Ecosystem

  • BA vs PM vs Product; SDLC (Agile/Waterfall/Hybrid)
  • Stakeholder identification, mapping & communication
  • Project context, scope, success metrics

Week 2

Requirements & Elicitation Techniques

  • Discovery workshops (JAD), interviewing, observation
  • From business needs → requirements → user stories
  • Notes → minutes → action items

Week 3

Documentation & Traceability

  • BRD/FRD, epics/features/stories hierarchy
  • MoSCoW prioritization, change control
  • Traceability with Excel/Jira/Azure DevOps

Week 4

Process & Data Modeling

  • BPMN swimlanes; As-Is vs To-Be
  • Use cases, context diagrams, DFD
  • ERD basics; reading schemas

Week 5

Tools & Systems Thinking

  • Jira + Confluence deep dive
  • Wireframes (Miro/Figma) and collaboration
  • APIs, integrations, non-functional requirements

Week 6

Validation, Testing & UAT

  • Acceptance criteria (Gherkin/Given-When-Then)
  • QA support: test cases, traceability
  • UAT planning, execution, and triage

Week 7

Capstone — Real BA Scenario

  • Define problem & scope; stakeholder roles
  • Create BRD, process model, and user stories
  • Prep presentation & demo outline

Week 8

Career & Presentation

  • Resume & LinkedIn alignment
  • Mock interviews (behavioral + case)
  • Portfolio showcase & final feedback

Frequently asked questions

Who is this for?

Career‑switchers and early‑career analysts who want practical BA skills and a portfolio in 8 weeks.

What are the prerequisites?

Comfort with basic computer skills. No coding required. Exposure to software projects helps but isn’t mandatory.

Is it live or self‑paced?

Live, online sessions with recordings provided. Weekly office hours included.
